reviewText: All was great service and delivery. I'm glad. Thank you
This short little DVD was perfect to introduce the novel The Witch of Blackbird Pond. It was an informative depiction of Puritan life.

This video is absolutely hilariously dated - but we enjoyed it thoroughly.  Not because it provided great insight into early New England life so much as it provided great insight into the attitudes and viewpoints of the 1950's.  Particularly entertaining and sad is the notion that an important role of Native Americans was to introduce great snack foods such as popcorn.
